An armed man opened fire at Bronx Lebanon Hospital in New York City, police said on Friday afternoon.According to local news reports a former employee of the hospital opened fire on the 16th and 17th floors with a rifle.The shooter was killed in the incident, the New York Police Commissioner said in a tweet at about 4 p.m. local time.Police did not say if anyone else was killed. Television stations showed the hospital surrounded by police cars and fire trucks. Police could be seen on the roof of the building with guns drawn.At least three doctors were shot, according to a report by The New York Times citing fire officials. The paper reported the shooter was described on police radio as a tall, thin man wearing a blue shirt and white lab coat. The paper reported that five to six people were wounded, according to preliminary reports.Local broadcasters reported that police officers were going from floor to floor inside the 120-year-old hospital looking for the suspect. Police warned people on Twitter to avoid the area.aw/jm (AP, Reuters, dpa, AFP)